  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 Pandemic Response for Extremely Vulnerable in Need Today (PREVINT)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 Pandemic Response for Extremely Vulnerable in Need Today (PREVINT) is a 6-month life-sustaining principled humanitarian response. Informed by first-hand studies and rapid needs analyses, the response addresses urgent humanitarian needs in the context of COVID-19 with the principle objective of: Local schemes and systems capacitated to minimize impact of COVID-19 on vulnerable and at-risk populations across Hama Governorate. To achieve this objective the response works towards two inter-related outcomes:


Outcome 1: Enhanced capacity of health facilities in Hama Governorate to respond to the COVID-19 pandemic. 
Under this outcome the Hama Central Laboratory and Salamieh National Hospital are equipped with COVID-19 medical equipment and supplies. 250 COVID-19 testing kits and one PCR device will be procured for Hama Central Laboratory and three ventilators will be procured for Salamieh National Hospital. Health specialists and technicians from each hospital will be trained by the WHO and MoH to properly use the acquired equipment as relevant to their work. 


Outcome 2: Increased capacity of target health workers to provide safe health services in the context of COVID-19.
Under this outcome, 1,920 health workers from both Salamieh National Hospital and Hama National Hospital will be equipped with PPE and trained on effective use as per WHO and MoH guidelines. 

Through these health interventions, the response will directly reach 182,163 people across Salamieh, Hama, As-Suqaylabiyah, Masyaf, and Muhradah Districts of Hama Governorate. 

As much as possible, interventions have been coordinated with the UN Health Cluster, the WHO, and the Ministry of Health at the national and provincial level and align with the SHF Allocation Paper and AKDN&#x2019;s Global and in-country response.</narrative>
  </description>
